The paper deals with the location problem of base stations in a wireless mobile backhaul network, which involves optimization of power consumption. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT) or Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of optimal transport theory, which is a mathematical framework for studying the transportation of mass or energy between different locations. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) or Discrete Mathematics (cs.DM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the placement of base stations in a way that minimizes power consumption, which is a problem that can be modeled using game theory. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the Game Theory (cs.GT) sub-category.
